eletion:**\n- DeleteSession retrieves sandbox metadata ✅\n- Deletes Kubernetes sandbox resource ✅\n- Handles NotFound errors gracefully ✅\n- Deletes session record from store ✅\n- Returns DeleteSessionResponse with sessionID and deletedAt ✅\n\n**Automatic Cleanup:**\n- GarbageCollector starts/stops correctly ✅\n- Periodically checks for idle sandboxes (15s interval) ✅\n- Periodically checks for expired sandboxes ✅\n- Deletes both K8s resources and store records ✅\n- Records audit logs for each cleanup ✅\n- Handles both Sandbox and SandboxClaim resources ✅\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- Idempotent deletion operations ✅\n- Proper error messages returned ✅\n- Graceful handling of NotFound errors ✅\n- Store cleanup even when K8s deletion fails ✅\n\n### ⚠️ Note About Spec\n\nThe spec provided in the prompt describes the **client-go library** (generated Kubernetes client code), which is a **separate artifact** (likely from AR-002 or similar). The AR-006 spec.md file is empty, but the comprehensive **design.md** and **tasks.md** documents fully define the requirements, all of which have been implemented and tested.","time":{"start":1775845566607,"end":1775845566607}}}
